details.address: 1031 Matthews-mint Hill Rd Suite B, Matthews, NC 28105
details.description: Locally owned café and coffee bar offering breakfast, lunch and custom crafted coffees in our relaxing dine-in space and outside patios. Our menu features made to order omelets, bagels, breakfast sandwiches, grain bowls, empanadas, burgers, wraps, and salads as well as vegetarian options and many café classics. Our espresso bar uses locally roasted, sustainably sourced beans from Magnolia Coffee in our Nitro, cold brew, specialty coffee drinks and retail whole bean coffees. We also serve protein shakes, frappes, smoothies, and fitness drinks. Are you looking to host an event or party? Come check out our venue spaces inside our café and neighboring co-work. We also offer full-service catering through our sister company TreeTop Catering.

reviews_data.review_text: Unfortunately, we had to wait 5 minutes for our coffee order because the only one who knew how to operate the espresso machine took a large phone order before she made our order. Then the extra hot latte came out luke warm and had to be remade. We usually get better service than this.

My cousin and I went here for a late lunch and it was fantastic. My chipotle chicken panini was perfect. Cajun bistro chips and steak fries were amazing. As was the green sauce we were suggested to try by the girl who brought our food. Sweet tea was on point. 10/10 will absolutely return (sorry for the half eaten sandwich pictures lol)
Had a great Cubano sandwich!

The Bacon, egg and cheese empanada is made with powdered eggs; I found it inedible.
The Cuban Empanada is served luke warm, cheese not melted.  When I asked server about it, he said it is not served as a hot item.
Disappointed for our first time visit.
The food was GREAT!  We enjoyed Empanadas(Chicken > Beef), French Toast, BLT and Buffalo Chicken Sandwich and Fries, Two iced coffees and Mango Lemonade. DELICIOUS
This place is so cute! Really good portion sizes and the breakfast sandwich was so good. Prices are reasonable.

Place is very nice and spacious, but I wouldn’t go there for food, only for coffee. I paid $18 for cheese sandwich with addition of grilled chicken and it was literally bread with cheese and chicken. Cut and dry and distasteful

This place looked cute, but the Brown Sugar Cinnamon latte tasted awful, all artificial gross that I can't finish it. The apple danish is moldy, nor was I offered to get it warmed up. I would have asked for a refund but I was just passing through and took it to go.

I stopped by Collective Café in Matthews and really enjoyed the experience. I ordered an iced tea and a cheese quesadilla.
The vibe of the café is really nice lots of people working on their laptops, so it definitely has a remote office kind of energy. It’s a great spot if you’re looking for a chill place to work or just unwind with some good food and a drink. I’d definitely come back!

reviews_data.review_text: Love the food and the people!

Yes, that is literally a massive cockroach..

I felt violently sick after seeing this…

When I complained to the manager/owner, he didn’t seem to care and just tried to give excuses rather than giving any form of apology or even offering any free anything as a gesture of Goodwill and apology…
Cool place. Great coffee shop. Food items good too. No GF snacks but other items like salads  and breakfast available

Overall this cafe is good. The food is good, the prices are reasonable especially for the portions. I took one star away because it was disappointing that one person in my group couldn’t eat because they have a tree nut allergy and this business stated they could not guarantee cross contamination. Also, if ordering coffee specify if you would like it hot or cold.
Really wish there was a gluten free bread option.
Great coffee. Kind staff. Relaxing atmosphere.

I got the overnight oats. Literally delicious I was not expecting that. The coffee was phenomenal. Plenty of seating inside.
Five ⭐️s.
The food is fantastic. I'm going back,l went back today took my wife with me thought she deserved it lol. The manager was excellent host, I'll return again

This cafe is a true hidden gem of Matthews, the atmosphere is incredible, a better "third place" than Starbucks by a longshot! They have a tasty & diverse menu and their beverages are remarkable. You've got to check it out!

reviews_data.review_text: Great place to meet friends or get some work done. Food and beverages are unique and delicious. Highly recommend!

Always a great experience at The Collective Cafe! The food and coffee are consistently delicious, and the staff is incredibly friendly and welcoming. Also love the workspace right next door—perfect for getting things done in a great atmosphere!

우리는 주말에 장소를 빌려서 작은 모임을 했습니다.
처음 이었는데 친절한 직원들과 아담하고 이쁘고 편한 공간이었어요.
다음에 평일에 재방문 하고 싶네요.
Might be my favorite coffee shop in Matthews. Coffee is amazing, nice seating area, breakfast was phenomenal. Fire spot for working as well. Little pricey but definitely worth it.
Fantastic empanadas!! Great ambiance. If you are looking for a home office break in Mathews, NC with delicious food and great service, this is your option.
If you are visiting NC - a must stop! Delicious, smooth and rich coffee. Food is scrumptious. We had to come back before departing.
Had a great lunch on day 1.  Went back on day 2 and had something different, still really pleased.  Will be back.
Great experience all around. Got breakfast and it was good. Server was attentive, atmosphere was welcoming. Really glad places like this exist that have a greater purpose.

Walking in; immediately greeted warmly by the staff!
The brewed coffee wasn't awesome (a little weak)... But when I traded out for an espresso drink, it was perfect!
I got the buffalo chicken sandwich... And I want you to know: it is the best buffalo sandwich I have ever had in my life. Check their kitchen for angels, because that sandwich made me see God.
Crispy chicken, generous sized cutlet... Tangy, spicy sauce. Blue cheese crumbles. I want to cry thinking about it again.
The fries, nice and hot, crispy.
The dressing on the side was the condiment I didn't feel I deserved. That blue cheese was something else.

I'm definitely coming back. I think I've found a second home here.

The entire area is warm, bright, and spacious.
It has the familiar comfort of a local coffee shop, and the variety of seating that's really like nowhere else. It's a very comfortable area.
I LOVE this place. And to know that the presence of the presence of the Lord is here is a bonus!!!! Such a hidden gem!

I ordered Today's Special Sandwich. It was served with Potato Salad, and Free Ice tea (other option was Lemonaid). Also I got the Iced Vanila Latte with Oatmilk.  My daughter liked the Sandwich (She's a little picky). And I liked my coffee & the Potato Salad!
The interior was good!! Especially I really liked the outdoor tables. There are many parking spot, so you don't need to worry about it. I will definitely visit again :)
I loved it! It's definitely a more trendy coffee shop, but there's lots of seating! The crossiant was super yummy, and I've been back several times since 😊

I recently visited for the first time. When I first walked in, the young lady behind the counter was assisting another customer, so it took a moment for her to acknowledge me. However, once she did, the service was good.

I decided to try a variety of empanadas since it was my first time having them. I ordered the broccoli and goat cheese, date and goat cheese, veggie egg and cheese, and strawberry and Nutella empanadas. My absolute favorite was the strawberry and Nutella. On the other hand, the broccoli in the broccoli and goat cheese empanada tasted like  frozen broccoli. The veggie egg and cheese empanada, however, had a nice kick of spice that I really enjoyed.

The atmosphere is great for meetups. Some areas are dimmer than others. I will definitely be back. I wish they served a banana nutella empanada!
Adorable and affordable! The café is casual vibes with great food and drinks!
Waited over 30 minutes to get 2 sandwiches and 2 empanadas. The staff was not very friendly, the food was good at least but overall not a great experience for the price tag.
Very satisfying omlets and wraps. I loved their Blizzard Brulle Latte.  Great customer service and a nice space to spend any time of the day there. Business or not, always welcome.
Hands down the best empanadas I have ever had here in Charlotte! Flaky crust well seasoned insides! Amazing. I drove 45 mins for these and it was worth the calories! lol!
Best kept secret in Matthews. But not for much longer.
Great spot for coffee, food, and atmosphere. The breakfast empanadas were delicious and latte was on point!
The food was incredible. I had a breakfast empanada and fresh fruit. I would give it a 10 if I could.
A wonderful addition to Matthews. I’ve been thoroughly impressed every time I’ve come. Highly recommend for a fresh lunch or a coffee—ambiance, space, and lots of accommodation for laptop work.
Very amazing coffee shop, has a straight up COUCH!!!!

Lovely ans cozy! Met here with my team for our weekly training, and enjoyed it very much. Even with being pack, it was still quiet and inviting (we may have been the loudest ones in there 😬). Service was great and so was the food. I didn't have coffee but enjoyed the Smores hot chocolate. Would certainly return. Thank you, Don, for the empanadas!!

reviews_data.review_text: Great place to eat, drink coffee or just work in a very warm atmosphere. Lots of comfortable seating areas, great vibe. The food was good as well! We spent 2 hrs working there.

The ambiance in nice. The matcha was highly overpriced. It’s $37 for a dozen empanadas. I asked for my matcha and she asked “sweetened” and I said yes not knowing it would be like 2 extra bucks. Then I realized it doesn’t even taste sweet and when I asked Rachel or whomever the girl was who made it she said “I put two squirts “ in there. Well I can’t taste it so just make it right. Really disappointed in customer service where I just added the free sugar on the side. $7 for a small matcha. Ridiculous. And I didn’t realize it’s a church for the unchurched. So you will be getting a push of religion specifically Christianity ✝️ with your matcha or coffee which is fine, but a bit…. Off putting. I think it would be fine if the two girls at the counter didn’t look as if they hated their jobs and were a bit kinder to the person purchasing since God is always with us, and watching. 🙄
Omelette was so good. Coffee is great and very reasonably priced.
Their mozza basil sandwich is so good! Love their food.
Expensive - coffee only spent over $7.00

Picked up a Mediterranean plate from here today. It was so delicious generously portioned and decently priced! Inside is super cute and has delicious pastries on display. Will definitely be back again!
Awesome coffee and breakfast sandwiches
Food was ok.
Me encantaron las empanadas de carne 😋
Amazing food with amazing service.

I ordered a latte with gingerbread syrup and gingerbread cold foam on top, I recommend that during the holidays. The quesadilla with sweet potato fries tasted great and the portion size was generous, I was full for the rest of the day after that. The staff is extremely friendly. The temperature in the building is just right. I’ve been twice and both times I was able to find seating. No complaints from me.

I’ve come here three times to get a quick coffee. Even with just one person ahead of me every time I stand in line for over 10 minutes and still wait to put in my order. I wound up leaving every time without coffee because it takes forever to just place an order. So frustrating. I’d love to support local businesses but I don’t feel like my time is valued when I’ve gone in here.

Last week I ordered a decaf americano and thought it tasted like old coffee. Ordered today and watched the barista pour drip decaf Coffee instead of expresso into my hot water. I asked if they don’t use expresso and she said she could and redid the drink. Hopefully management sees this review and the baristas properly make the drinks in the future. I am charged an extra $1.20 for an expresso or drink and am being served water down stale drip coffee.
Their salmon salad is the best!
Great looking place but drinks are a hit pricey and the chai is too sweet
Best lunch spot in Matthews!

I'm obsessed with their empanadas. Had an amazing breakfast wrap and coffee was good. Loved the space too, would recommend to anyone looking for a chill coffee shop to get work done.. Very good breakfast and ambiance.

This place is simply amazing! I wanted a local spot that wasn't too busy to get some food and do some remote work. The food was awesome and well presented. The staff were cordial  and efficient. And the atmosphere was warm and inviting.

Great cafe for grabbing breakfast or lunch. Awesome environment for working remotely or studying, although busy, usually plenty of space. They have the option next door to rent office space and meeting rooms. Menu posted is out of date, all items are up a few dollars, posting prices as of today.
I like this place. Each staff member is so cute and quirky I love it feels like I fit right in I live the vibes but tab,es are rlly close togetHer
Had no idea this place even existed.  Had a Caesar salad with chicken,  good portion size and came out quickly.  plenty of parking and overall a friendly experience.

As a Realtor, this has quickly become my go-to spot for breakfast meetings or a break between showings. The calm, relaxing atmosphere is ideal for catching up with clients over coffee or discussing the details of a transaction in a peaceful setting. Whether I’m meeting with clients or taking a moment to recharge, this place always hits the mark. #carlamyagent
Amazing food and drinks. Friendly, laid back atmosphere. Service could be a little faster.

My wife and I both ordered the french toast. She got some coffe and I got the strawberry mango smoothie.

Great place, great owners and great food.
Amazing café, food and coffee delicious! Rachel made some amazing sandwiches! 10/10
Great, laid back spot for breakfast.

Incredible place… I’m from Phoenix, visiting friends and I went to Elevation church …. They told me I had to come here and I loved  it… baristas made awesome drinks… the manager from Peru is the sweetest woman ever… my favorite cafe is now in Charlotte! Got to come back… God Bless Collective Cafe!

My boyfriend and I stopped by today for a quick snack before heading out. The manager was at the register and was incredibly friendly. He recommended the empanadas, mentioning they’re a top seller, so we decided to try them. We got the chicken, guava and cheese, and beef empanadas, which came with a cilantro dip. They were delicious—some of the best empanadas I’ve ever had and not a bad price either! Definitely coming back again!
This place was a really nice find. Perfect to catch up with a friend. Good foods and lots of sweet coffee options.

Wish we lived closer to this place so we could come more often! The breakfast wrap is outstanding, the baked goods are lovely, and the drinks are great too. Everything always comes out perfectly and the staff is excellent.
Love this place! Great atmosphere, coffee is delicious, and portions are huge. Employees are super nice too!
Great empanada and smoothie!!

Today, after my inaugural visit to The Collective Café, I concluded that the food & beverage items are delectable, the ambiance synergistic, and their pricing competitive. Indeed, "a refreshing novelty that has the potential to become addictive!" KUDOS to the adept staff & mgmt - my guest and I thoroughly enjoyed the experience.
JBurch
Customer service was absolutely amazing and their food was so good if you come to Matthews must check out

Excellent coffee with great service. Large menu with a lot of options and the food was delicious.
Support this local hidden gem, you won't regret it.

I’d like to start off by saying this place has a very great atmosphere and I would definitely recommend going here if you want a workspace. This place is even kind of connected to a business that rents out rooms so that people can collaborate in them.

I would also say that going to a place to grab regular tea or coffee shouldn’t really come with too much expections , so here that would be great also. That is why I gave this place three stars instead of two.

My boyfriend was actually pretty upset at our visit to this place. When our drinks were serve, they were given sloppy you have to go up and grab them and he said that both drinks were sitting in a puddle that he basically cleaned up while also cleaning up our drinks , just felt like since it was basically Starbucks prices that you know it should be about the same service as Starbucks. But beyond this, he became more disappointed when both of our food wasn’t good. His fruit wasn’t ripe, it was like halfway frozen or something… and my breakfast burrito had almost no flavor.

The people that work here are pretty awesome though .

While in the area had some free time so decided to check this place out for a latte. Space seems super cool, and the food smells were good (I did not have any food), but unfortunately the latte I had was horrid. Apparently “small latte, extra shot, extra hot” translates to “sour espresso in bath of luke warm milk”. Maybe they just haven’t dialed in their machine in a while….  but it’s waaaaaay off.
Cutest little cafe, great food

My Husband and I went to this cafe and we grabbed their Chai Latte & Mint tea and it was really good. We came  second time for lunch and I got their Burger and my husband got their chipotle chicken sandwich. Wow, 1000/10, we definitely found our favorite lunch spot!

The collective café serves good drinks and has even better customer service. I personally like their seasonal lattes. The food is usually good as well, I definitely recommend their empanadas. As for the atmosphere I think that it is the perfect place to meet a friend or work on a project. All together a great establishment. Cheers.

Shout out to Thai! I don't know if that's his name is spelled, but it's how it sounds. Thai and all the staff always create a beautiful service experience that is reminiscent of fine dining. In addition to the service, they cook real food - tastes like home but even better - with delicious coffee. I love coming here, it's my forever "go to" spot!

I had the pleasure of attending a private event there! The service exceeded my expectations.  The female attendant who worked at the party deserves a perfect 10. She was very pleasant, very accommodating, and went above and beyond. I highly recommend this venue for intimate events

reviews_data.review_text: Great place for meetup or regular visits. Great coffee options and other specialty drinks. Warm but rustic decor makes for great experience. Expansive menu with unique offerings. Had the chicken empanadas and the grilled chicken sandwich, both tasty! There was plenty of room to spread out at tables or cushy chairs and have privacy for studying , reading or having that conference call without disturbing others or being disturbed. The 'Church for the UnChurched chalk board was great touch, blending Biblical quotes with other inspirational messages of encouragement may also provide a peek into the cafe's vibe and or ownership

Good food and coffee

They serve fresh, hot food and have friendly service.  I'll be back.
Enjoyed it thoroughly.  Been a few times with different people.  They use local roasters for their coffee and espresso beans.  The staff is very welcoming and accommodating.

My experience at The Collective Cafe was so-so at best and the customer service was meh. I ordered a hot chai which was pretty good but the empanadas I ordered weren't very appetizing. They fried the living heck out of the empanadas to the point where they were almost inedible. If I didn't pay for these, then I probably wouldn't have eaten them. I ordered the following empanadas:  nutella & strawberry, date & goat cheese, and guava & cheese. The date and goat cheese lost most of its filling while being fried and the nutella & strawberry also had minimal filling. The guava & cheese had a good amount of filling but it was mostly just cheese. I have had my fair share of empanadas and these probably rank as some of the worst unfortunately.
I love the atmosphere of this place. Sometimes it gets a little crowded, but when I get the comfy seats I'm happy.
Good food
This was a fun place! The workers are extremely nice and the place is spaciousness!
Very nice place and the food was great 😊
Excellent coffee with nice food options. The Internet and atmosphere are great for getting some work done while enjoying a coffee.
Great cafe. They got plenty of food and drink options, not really overpriced either. Very cute inside and I'm pretty sure it's owned by the church right next to it. Would highly recommend this place

I have only ever ordered on DoorDash and my order is messed up often!! I have even called to speak to the Manager several times and they are never there per the girl that answers. I just ordered empanada that is supposed to come with green sauce which they often do not include so I made a point to put it on notes and I see it on receipt but once again NO green sauce. Also ordered a bacon egg and cheese croissant. Requested Mayo because they sent once on their own but no Mayo and no yogurt/fruit which is supposed to come with it. I like the food but when you mess up 50% of the time it makes me want to order from somewhere else.

Always decent seating, no pressure, short lines, good parking, and decent products.  Coffee is 4 out of 5, but very acceptable, though if you have a very sophisticated request, these aren't top-level baristas that can create anything you want.  I just want a decent drip coffee and get that every time. Overall, it is a much more pleasant experience than most coffee shops.
This quiet little cafe has excellent coffee and a nice assortment of breakfast items & pastries. A calm atmosphere to get some remote work done or just surf the net and enjoy some serenity..

I’m trying to find my breakfast place and this might be it. Easy ordering and take a number, they’ll bring you your food. Plenty of seating areas. Breakfast burrito was awesome and very filling.  I’ll be back.

Great little place to have coffee or get a bite to eat. I enjoyed their chicken salad sandwich on a croissant and their fries. The place is usually pretty quiet. So it's nice just to go and relax a bit.

Unreal food. As an Aussie travelling in the US, it’s tough to find yummy food that isn’t covered in oil & sugar.
Had a chipotle chicken panini - Tasted unreal, and didn’t feel heavy like most other US food.
Staff also super friendly, which was awesome. Well done.
A great little breakfast or lucky place.
If only the staff were as good as the empanadas...
Traveling from Charlotte to Oak Island and this turned out to be a great little place!
Where you would go for a hot drink on a hot day. A/C was blasting in a good way. A nice cardigan if you're drinking an iced drink would help. I would take my friends here after lunch any day.
New favorite place! absolutely love the food! Buffalo Chicken (fried) sandwich is great! wedge fries are the best! Just had the empanadas (bacon, egg, and cheese)(chicken). i will be back for more!!!

A very nice place! Quiet place, nice and chill atmosphere. I had 2 empanadas and a Chai latte and everything was great. The staff is cheery and nice and the prices are good. I will definitely come back
Great food, people, and prices !!!

Fantastic spot for me and my work mates. The food is delicious and they offer wide open parking lot, which is a huge plus. When you walk inside, place your order at the register, get a number, find a table and voila¡! Highly recommend, but try not to tell everyone.
Great coffee shop for working and holding meetings.
I ordered a Smoky chipotle chicken panini sandwich today.  It was absolutely delicious !!! Service was fast and courteous.  I definitely have a new favorite place !!

Good iced lattes and surprisingly tasty fries. They don’t really call your name when your coffee is ready - if they do, it’s inaudible. Stand by the counter to wait for your coffee. The chicken panini tasted good, but its made with deli meat vs an actual chicken breast like you’d expect. Burger was good. Couldn’t connect to WiFi tho
Service and atmosphere are really nice.  Good food all the way around.  Also a great cup of coffee.  Would highly recommend the empanadas. 😁

The service, space, and strawberry pina colada was as expected. However today, their wifi is not working. I was very patient and have tried both on my laptop and phone. Their recommended solution was to hotspot myself.

I’m very disappointed especially since I came to get some computer work done.  I think a place that advertises to be a working space should have their wifi functioning therefore, I rate this below average.

I hope they get this worked out.
First time here and WOW, Life changing. The barista at the counter awooga. Blond girls with white eye shadow. Cannot wait to eat another chicken salad sandwich #yummers

As I waited at Jiffy Lube in Matthews, NC, I stumbled upon a hidden gem right around the corner—an exquisite coffee shop and restaurant that turned out to be a delightful surprise. From the moment I stepped inside The Collective Cafe, I knew I was in for a culinary treat.

The ambiance of the place was warm and inviting, with its cozy decor and comfortable seating. The aroma of freshly brewed coffee filled the air, instantly tantalizing my senses. The friendly and attentive staff greeted me with genuine smiles, making me feel right at home.

Being a coffee lover, I couldn't resist trying their specialty brews. The barista expertly prepared my cappuccino, and with the first sip, I was transported to coffee heaven. The smooth, rich flavors and perfect balance of the espresso and velvety foam were simply divine. It was evident that they took great pride in their coffee craftsmanship.

As I perused the menu, I discovered a wide array of delectable dishes to choose from. The menu showcased a fusion of international flavors, promising a culinary adventure. The presentation was impeccable, and with every bite, I savored the explosion of tastes and textures. It was evident that the chef had a passion for creating culinary masterpieces.

What truly impressed me was their commitment to sourcing local and organic ingredients. They emphasized sustainability and showcased seasonal produce, which added an extra layer of freshness and vibrancy to each dish. The attention to detail was evident not only in the taste but also in the visual appeal of the food.

The service was exceptional throughout my visit. The staff members were knowledgeable about the menu, and they were more than willing to provide recommendations based on personal preferences. The wait time for my food was minimal, and my server ensured that I had everything I needed to make my dining experience memorable.

Overall, my unplanned visit turned out to be a culinary adventure that surpassed my expectations. The combination of exceptional coffee, tantalizing flavors, and attentive service made it a standout dining experience in Matthews, NC. Whether you're seeking a cozy coffee spot or a place to indulge in extraordinary cuisine, I highly recommend visiting this place. It's a true gem that deserves recognition for its outstanding culinary offerings and warm hospitality.
Great vibe and helpful staff. Great place to focus and get great food.
I love Collective Cafe from the food to the atmosphere. I enjoy having meals here and meeting others for coffee.
My iced caramel latte was delicious and the service was amazing!
I loved the vibe of collective, it was super inviting. As a person who has gone to a lot of coffee shops, I really enjoyed sitting there with my friends and the drinks were good.

Definitely a “no regret” location.

It's definitely a spot to save to your favorites list. Tried the egg white veggie omlette and it was excellent. Also tried 2 different hot drinks, both were very good. Staff are very friendly and easy going.

Food is good ,

I used to really love this place, and I still do to some extent. I love the veggie scramble wrap. I still order it, but there's one problem. This dish is supposed to come with salsa and a fruit cup. It used to consistently always be delivered with both of those items, but in the past few months there is now only a 10% chance that, if ordered, the wrap will come with salsa and a fruit cup. More often than not, I only get the wrap. It's pretty disappointing, because the salsa essentially made that wrap so delicious. Without it, it's rather bland. I make do by adding salt or my own hot sauce, but it isn't the same. Additionally, in the past few months every single time I get this wrap, it has been increasingly greasy. When I pick it up, it literally drips grease. "No problem," I thought initially, "I'll just wipe up the excess with a napkin." Nope. It's as if the grease is coming from some source of infinite grease within the wrap. I wish they would pay more attention when making these, and when packing them up for delivery. It makes it less enjoyable when they don't. I don't know if they got a new cook/chef recently, or what, but if that is the case, I hope they get them trained up pretty soon. I miss my yummy veggie scramble wrap.

raw_data.description: Locally owned café and coffee bar offering breakfast, lunch and custom crafted coffees in our relaxing dine-in space and outside patios. Our menu features made to order omelets, bagels, breakfast sandwiches, grain bowls, empanadas, burgers, wraps, and salads as well as vegetarian options and many café classics. Our espresso bar uses locally roasted, sustainably sourced beans from Magnolia Coffee in our Nitro, cold brew, specialty coffee drinks and retail whole bean coffees. We also serve protein shakes, frappes, smoothies, and fitness drinks. Are you looking to host an event or party? Come check out our venue spaces inside our café and neighboring co-work. We also offer full-service catering through our sister company TreeTop Catering.

Really disappointed in customer service where I just added the free sugar on the side. $7 for a small matcha. Ridiculous. And I didn’t realize it’s a church for the unchurched. So you will be getting a push of religion specifically Christianity ✝️ with your matcha or coffee which is fine, but a bit…. Off putting. As I waited at Jiffy Lube in Matthews, NC, I stumbled upon a hidden gem right around the corner—an exquisite coffee shop and restaurant that turned out to be a delightful surprise. From the moment I stepped inside The Collective Cafe, I knew I was in for a culinary treat.

The ambiance of the place was warm and inviting, with its cozy decor and comfortable seating. The aroma of freshly brewed coffee filled the air, instantly tantalizing my senses. The friendly and attentive staff greeted me with genuine smiles, making me feel right at home.

Being a coffee lover, I couldn't resist trying their specialty brews. The barista expertly prepared my cappuccino, and with the first sip, I was transported to coffee heaven. The smooth, rich flavors and perfect balance of the espresso and velvety foam were simply divine. It was evident that they took great pride in their coffee craftsmanship.

As I perused the menu, I discovered a wide array of delectable dishes to choose from. The menu showcased a fusion of international flavors, promising a culinary adventure. The presentation was impeccable, and with every bite, I savored the explosion of tastes and textures. It was evident that the chef had a passion for creating culinary masterpieces.

What truly impressed me was their commitment to sourcing local and organic ingredients. They emphasized sustainability and showcased seasonal produce, which added an extra layer of freshness and vibrancy to each dish. The attention to detail was evident not only in the taste but also in the visual appeal of the food.

The service was exceptional throughout my visit. The staff members were knowledgeable about the menu, and they were more than willing to provide recommendations based on personal preferences. The wait time for my food was minimal, and my server ensured that I had everything I needed to make my dining experience memorable.

Overall, my unplanned visit turned out to be a culinary adventure that surpassed my expectations. The combination of exceptional coffee, tantalizing flavors, and attentive service made it a standout dining experience in Matthews, NC. Whether you're seeking a cozy coffee spot or a place to indulge in extraordinary cuisine, I highly recommend visiting this place. It's a true gem that deserves recognition for its outstanding culinary offerings and warm hospitality.

I used to really love this place, and I still do to some extent. I love the veggie scramble wrap. I still order it, but there's one problem. This dish is supposed to come with salsa and a fruit cup. It used to consistently always be delivered with both of those items, but in the past few months there is now only a 10% chance that, if ordered, the wrap will come with salsa and a fruit cup. More often than not, I only get the wrap. It's pretty disappointing, because the salsa essentially made that wrap so delicious. Without it, it's rather bland. I make do by adding salt or my own hot sauce, but it isn't the same. Additionally, in the past few months every single time I get this wrap, it has been increasingly greasy. When I pick it up, it literally drips grease. "No problem," I thought initially, "I'll just wipe up the excess with a napkin." Nope. It's as if the grease is coming from some source of infinite grease within the wrap. I wish they would pay more attention when making these, and when packing them up for delivery. It makes it less enjoyable when they don't. I don't know if they got a new cook/chef recently, or what, but if that is the case, I hope they get them trained up pretty soon.
